pd_0_com_0text: Aren't you a sight for sore eyes?
pd_1_com_0text: So eager to get your bottom kicked at cards?
pd_1_com_1text: Have you finally accepted how much you love my dashing personality?
pd_4_com_0text: No, but I do love some peace and quiet that will come after I don’t have to worry about you.
pd_5_com_0text: Celebrating your victory before actually winning? That never goes wrong.
pd_6_com_0text: You are late. What have you been doing?
pd_7_com_0text: Just catching up on some reading.
pd_8_com_0text: Ah, of course. I forgot you don’t have much entertainment in that room.
pd_9_com_1text: I have myself and my quick wit. What more would I desire?
pd_10_com_0text: Don’t look at me like that. It is not my responsibility to amuse you.
pd_11_com_0text: It should be. It’s been so long, I can’t even remember the last time I had guests!
pd_13_com_0text: With your memory span of a goldfish? Tragic indeed.
pd_16_com_0text: And your recognition of my talents.
pd_19_com_0text: Anyway. Should we start the game?
pd_20_com_0text: Yes, thanks for dealing the hands already.
pd_21_com_0text: You look nervous. Afraid your gift will fail you this time?
pd_22_com_0text: It will not fail me. The only time I lost was because of your stupid mistake.
pd_23_com_0text: It’s curious how you blame your loss on the disappearance of one card.
pd_23_com_1text: How can you be so sure it was a mistake?
pd_24_com_1text: You assured me you did not cheat.
pd_26_com_0text: It gave me some food for thought. This gift you keep bragging about… You really do have it, don’t you?
pd_27_com_0text: I was always upfront about it. It is not my fault you never listened.
pd_28_com_0text: You were upfront about it with the intention of hiding it. How noble.
pd_28_com_1text: In my defense, it is quite difficult to believe such a gift exists.
pd_29_com_0text: A person sees what they want to see. I was honest. That’s all that matters.
pd_30_com_0text: I don’t blame you. Most people don’t listen either.
pd_31_com_0text: This gift is quite unfair, don’t you think?
pd_32_com_0text: Good thing I took it upon myself to even out the playing field.
pd_34_com_0text: I thought it would be fair if I removed a certain powerful card that made it way easier for you to win with your luck.
pd_35_com_0text: And you are only telling me that now?
pd_36_com_0text: Stop the game. I do not wish to continue.
pd_37_com_0text: You know the rules, Daemon. Once we start the game, we have to finish it.
pd_38_com_0text: You cheating bastard. I should have seen this coming.
pd_38_com_1text: This is not the game we agreed on.
pd_39_com_0text: This is the one you get.
pd_39_com_1text: Too bad you tried to trick me with your gift.
pd_40_com_0text: I can still win. Your trick is nothing but a minor hiccup in my plan.
pd_41_com_0text: Oh? Are you saying you’ve suddenly mastered cards?
pd_42_com_0text: I have played many games. I know what I’m doing.
pd_43_com_0text: Someone who relied only on luck to guide him will not have much skill, don’t you think?
pd_44_com_0text: Shut up. Just… shut up. You are trying to throw me off.
pd_47_com_0text: Is this it? Not even going to talk to me?
pd_48_com_0text: You are gloating like you’ve already won, yet we still have a whole game ahead of us.
pd_49_com_0text: You are so nervous, I can’t help but play with you a little.
pd_49_com_1text: It is only fair, don’t you think? You’ve kept me here for so long. How long has it been exactly?
pd_54_com_0text: It’s always about you and your games.
pd_55_com_0text: I didn’t start this game, Daemon. You did.
pd_58_com_0text: No… No, this can’t be happening...
pd_62_com_0text: Your luck has left you after all.
pd_63_com_0text: No, I can still win..! Just give me one more chance!
pd_64_com_0text: You had all the time in the world, Daemon, but nothing is eternal. It was bound to run out.
pd_65_com_0text: You still need me to get out! If we can make one more deal..!
pd_66_com_0text: Oh, do not worry about me. Your little room of tricks is nothing for me, now that my memories are rushing back.
pd_67_com_0text: But you… You put up quite a fight. It’s admirable, really.
pd_68_com_0text: I never would have thought I could lose my eternal knowledge to a mortal.
pd_69_com_0text: This whole experience has been quite humbling. I should probably thank you. You’ve opened up my eyes to things I never thought could happen.
pd_71_com_0text: Oh, Daemon, dear… Do not cry.
pd_72_com_0text: I will make sure your soul gets the most special place in my collection.
